Integration tests exercising `hook::run`, `session` persistence, and CLI `dispatch` together, all against an in-memory `FakeEnv` (no real filesystem) — verifies that Claude-hook injection and manual `ctx-context <path>` CLI invocations share the same per-session dedup ledger.

`FakeEnv` is a flat `BTreeMap<String, Vec<u8>>` keyed by repo-relative path string, implementing `ctx_context::env::Env`; `is_dir` is inferred from key-prefix matching (`"{path}/"`), not stored separately. `FakeEnv::seeded()` builds a fixed tree: root and `crates/foo` each have `rollup.ctx`+`intent.md`, plus a leaf `.ctx` for `bar.rs`, and two sibling source files `bar.rs`/`baz.rs` (only `bar.rs` has a leaf ctx). Tests rely on this exact seeded layout — e.g. `baz.rs` intentionally has no leaf so its dedup case yields "nothing to inject."

Key invariants under test, not obvious from other files: hook injection dedups per `session_id`, keyed by ancestor chain already shown, so a sibling file read in the same session only injects newly-uncovered levels; a different `session_id` starts fresh. Session state lives at `.context/.cache/hook-<session_id>.json` (path format asserted directly in `path_mode_without_session_env_leaves_no_session_state` and `corrupt_session_state_reads_as_empty`) — changing that path template breaks these tests silently since they hardcode it via `RepoPath::parse`. Corrupt/unparseable session state must be treated as empty (fail-open), so `hook::run` still injects rather than erroring. CLI path-mode dispatch (`dispatch(&env, base, cli, "", &mut out)`) shares the *same* session ledger as the hook when `session::ENV_SESSION_ID` env var is set (via `FakeEnv::set_var`), and repeat calls with nothing new to add produce literal text containing `"no new context"`. Without that env var set, no session file is written at all — path mode is stateless per invocation in that case.

Depends on `clap::Parser` for constructing `Cli` via `Cli::parse_from`, and directly exercises `ctx_context::{hook, session, cli::dispatch, env::Env, error::CtxError, repo_path::RepoPath}` — any signature change to `hook::run`, `session::load`, or `dispatch` breaks this file first.